Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_object_name(25.10)                                  get_object_name(25.10)

Name
       get_object_name  -  Returns  the name of the object(s) contained in the
       specified collections

Syntax
        get_object_name

       [-help]

       <collection>

       Returns the name of the object(s) contained in  the  specified  collec-
       tions.

       By  default,  the command hides escape characters in the output. To en-
       able printing of escape characters in the  output,  you  can  set  tim-
       ing_enable_get_object_escaped_name_backward_compatible  global variable
       to true.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <collection>
              Specifies multiple collections that contain objects.

Examples
              * The following command returns a tcl list of  names  which  can
                match the collection inputs:

                get_object_name [get_cells and*]

              * The  following command defines a variable called endpoint_list
                to store endpoints with the ten worst slacks:

                set endpoint_list [get_object_name [get_property \

                      [report_timing  -collection  -max_points   10]   captur-
                ing_point]]

Related Information
              * query_objects

